  "title": "Part-Time Marketing & Centre Support Assistant",
  "description": "<p>Location: Hybrid (remote + onsite at Iron Scholars, Aljunied)</p><p>Compensation: $400-$600/month (task-based & centre management) + $20 commission per successful enrolment after a trial class, where applicable</p><p>Commitment: Minimum 1 year</p><p><strong>About Us</strong></p><p>Iron Scholars is a growing enrichment centre dedicated to innovative learning experiences for children. We’re looking for a proactive, creative, and trustworthy individual to join our team and help us expand our reach while supporting centre operations.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>• \tMarketing & Outreach (Main Focus): Drive visibility of the centre, generate leads, and support conversion into enrolments.</p><p>• \tSocial Media Content Creation: Produce simple but engaging posts, graphics, and videos to build our online presence.</p><p>• \tCentre Management Support: Oversee classes on some weekends and other required days, with simple administrative tasks.</p><p>• \tContent Recording: Capture video footage during class sessions for promotional and educational use.</p><p><strong>What We’re Looking For</strong></p><p>• \tHighly agile, adaptable, and trustworthy self-starter.</p><p>• \tEfficient and proactive in taking on evolving tasks as the centre grows.</p><p>• \tExperience in content creation and basic graphic design.</p><p>• \tStrong communication skills; able to build rapport with parents and children.</p><p>• \tPassion for education and working with kids.</p><p>• \tFlexible and comfortable with hybrid work arrangements.</p><p><strong>Why Join Us</strong></p><p>• \tOpportunity to make a real impact in a growing education centre.</p><p>• \tFlexible hybrid role with varied responsibilities.</p><p>• \tWarm, collaborative environment where creativity and initiative are valued.</p><p>• \t1-year commitment with added commission incentives for enrolment conversions.<br /></p><p><strong>Who This Role Might Be Good For</strong></p><p>• \tUniversity students looking for flexible, meaningful part-time work that builds marketing and communication skills.</p><p>• \tMothers or caregivers seeking extra income with manageable hours and a family-friendly environment.</p><p>• \tYoung professionals wanting to gain experience in marketing, outreach, and education while working in a growing centre.</p><p>• \tFreelancers/creatives who enjoy content creation and want steady, predictable side income.</p>",
